<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-02-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="257" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                    <head>No. 255.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bancroft</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-02-11"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 11,
                            1874</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 648.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your No. 562, of the 16th ultimo,
                        relating to the final denial by the proper authorities of reports concerning
                        negotiations between Germany and Denmark respecting the cession of the
                        Danish West Indies, I have to request you to be watchful in case any
                        negotiation of that character should occur.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>